# Card Quality Evaluation Framework

## Overview

This framework defines how to evaluate existing cards and generate new ones. Each category has different goals, so the same question can be excellent for one category and terrible for another.

## Common Rules (All Categories)

### Required (Pass/Fail)

| Rule | Description |
|------|-------------|
| **Grammar** | No spelling errors, proper punctuation, question marks where needed |
| **Clarity** | Meaning is unambiguous, easy to understand on first read |
| **Open-ended** | Invites discussion or action, not just yes/no answers |
| **Appropriate** | No hate speech, discrimination, or content that could cause harm |

### Universal Quality Metrics (1-5 scale)

| Metric | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **Uniqueness** | Not a cliché or overused question |
| **Engagement** | Will people actually want to answer/discuss this? |
| **Replayability** | Can this card be drawn multiple times without getting stale? |

